name: Velut inter ignis luna minors
description:
2400x2400, graphite on paper.

"Velut inter ignis..." is taken from the Horace's "Odes" (23 BC); it is a latin sentence which means "like the moon among the smaller stars", that's to say, the moon is a star bigger than the others, so shines more than them. Or it could mean that the weaker one dies. Also, this verse is inscribed on the back of Hole's "Retard Girl" cover art. The lyrics narrate a girl being bullied on a school playground. In 2010, Courtney Love said she had written the song after a group of men tried to gang rape her while she was working at a bikini-bar in Los Angeles.
